 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Excel Retriever MCP Server - Demo\\n",
    "\\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates how to use the **Excel Retriever MCP Server** - a tool that extracts and queries data from Excel files using the docling library. This solves the problem of Copilot and other LLMs struggling to properly extract structured data from Excel files.\\n",
    "\\n",
    "## How This Notebook Works\\n",
    "\\n",
    "This notebook uses **Jupyter magic functions** (`%%writefile`) to create the MCP server files automatically. When you run the cells below, they will:\\n",
    "1. Create a `mcp_project/` folder to isolate the server code\\n",
    "2. Generate `excel_server.py` - the main MCP server with 6 tools\\n",
    "3. Generate `pyproject.toml` - project configuration with dependencies\\n",
    "\\n",
    "**Note:** The magic function `%%writefile` saves the cell content to a file instead of executing it in the notebook. You will use the MCP Inspector (a UI tool) to interact with the server.\\n",
    "\\n",
    "## Folder Structure After Setup\\n",
    "\\n",
    "```\\n",
    "excel_retriever/\\n",
    "├── mcp_project/          # Created by this notebook\\n",
    "│   ├── excel_server.py   # MCP server (generated by %%writefile)\\n",
    "│   └── pyproject.toml     # Dependencies (generated by %%writefile)\\n",
    "├── excel_files/          # Your Excel files go here\\n",
    "├── create_sample_data.py # Sample data generator (at root level)\\n",
    "├── demo_notebook.ipynb   # This notebook\\n",
    "├── demo_instructions.md  # Markdown version of instructions\\n",
    "└── README.md            # Quick reference\\n",
    "```\\n",
    "\\n",
    "## What is MCP?\\n",
    "\\n",
    "Model Context Protocol (MCP) is a standard for connecting AI assistants to external tools and data sources. This server exposes tools that can:\\n",
    "- **list_excel_files** - List all Excel files in a directory\\n",
    "- **extract_excel_content** - Extract full content from an Excel file\\n",
    "- **query_excel_data** - Query specific information from Excel\\n",
    "- **get_excel_summary** - Get file structure summary\\n",
    "- **convert_excel_to_csv** - Convert Excel sheets to CSV\\n",
    "- **convert_excel_to_json** - Convert Excel sheets to JSON\\n",
    "\\n",
    "## OpenSearch Integration (Optional - For Large Files)\\n",
    "\\n",
    "For very large Excel files (100k+ rows), the server supports **OpenSearch integration**:\\n",
    "\\n",
    "- **index_excel_in_opensearch** - Index Excel data for fast searching\\n",
    "- **search_excel_opensearch** - Search indexed data with hybrid search\\n",
    "- **list_opensearch_indices** - List all indexed Excel files\\n",
    "\\n",
    "**Why OpenSearch?**\\n",
    "- Handles massive Excel files that won't fit in memory\\n",
    "- Fast hybrid search (keyword + text matching)\\n",
    "- Relevance scoring with highlights\\n",
    "\\n",
    "## Prerequisites\\n",
    "\\n",
    "You need either **uv** (recommended) or **pip** installed to run this server."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\\n",
    "\\n",
    "## Step 1: Install uv (Recommended)\\n",
    "\\n",
    "**uv** is a fast Python package manager and environment manager. It's the recommended way to run MCP servers.\\n",
    "\\n",
    "### Option A: Install uv (if not already installed)\\n",
    "\\n",
    "**macOS/Linux:**\\n",
    "```bash\\n",
    "curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh\\n",
    "```\\n",
    "\\n",
    "**Windows:**\\n",
    "```powershell\\n",
    "powershell -ExecutionPolicy ByPass -c \\"irm https://astral.sh/uv/install.ps1 | iex\\"\\n",
    "```\\n",
    "\\n",
    "After installation, restart your terminal or run:\\n",
    "```bash\\n",
    "source ~/.zshrc  # macOS/Linux\\n",
    "```\\n",
    "\\n",
    "### Option B: Use pip instead\\n",
    "\\n",
    "If you prefer not to use uv, ensure you have Python 3.10+ and pip installed:\\n",
    "```bash\\n",
    "python3 --version  # Should be 3.10 or higher\\n",
    "pip --version\\n",
    "```\\n",
    "\\n",
    "Install pip if needed:\\n",
    "- **macOS**: `python3 -m ensurepip --upgrade`\\n",
    "- **Ubuntu/Debian**: `sudo apt install python3-pip`\\n",
    "- **Windows**: pip comes with Python installer"
   ]
