    "---\\n",
    "\\n",
    "## Step 6: Launch the MCP Inspector and Test the Server\\n",
    "\\n",
    "The **MCP Inspector** is a UI tool for testing MCP servers interactively. You do NOT need to run the server separately first - the Inspector will start it for you!\\n",
    "\\n",
    "### Prerequisites\\n",
    "\\n",
    "You need **Node.js** installed to run the Inspector:\\n",
    "\\n",
    "**Check if Node.js is installed:**\\n",
    "```bash\\n",
    "node --version\\n",
    "npx --version\\n",
    "```\\n",
    "\\n",
    "**Install Node.js if needed:**\\n",
    "- **macOS**: `brew install node`\\n",
    "- **Ubuntu/Debian**: `sudo apt install nodejs npm`\\n",
    "- **Windows**: Download from [nodejs.org](https://nodejs.org)\\n",
    "\\n",
    "### Start the Inspector\\n",
    "\\n",
    "**Important:** Run this command from the `mcp_project` folder.\\n",
    "\\n",
    "Open a terminal and run:\\n",
    "\\n",
    "**Using uv:**\\n",
    "```bash\\n",
    "cd mcp_project\\n",
    "npx @modelcontextprotocol/inspector uv run excel_server.py\\n",
    "```\\n",
    "\\n",
    "**Using Python:**\\n",
    "```bash\\n",
    "cd mcp_project\\n",
    "npx @modelcontextprotocol/inspector python excel_server.py\\n",
    "```\\n",
    "\\n",
    "**What happens:**\\n",
    "1. The Inspector starts the MCP server automatically\\n",
    "2. The Inspector displays a URL (usually http://localhost:5173)\\n",
    "3. Open that URL in your browser\\n",
    "4. You can now test all the tools interactively!\\n",
    "\\n",
    "### Inspector Configuration\\n",
    "\\n",
    "In the Inspector UI, make sure these settings are correct:\\n",
    "\\n",
    "| Setting | Value (uv) | Value (pip) |\\n",
    "|---------|------------|-------------|\\n",
    "| **Command** | `uv` | `python` |\\n",
    "| **Arguments** | `run excel_server.py` | `excel_server.py` |\\n",
    "\\n",
    "Click **\\"Connect\\"** or **\\"Restart\\"** to connect to the server."
   ]
