    "---\\n",
    "\\n",
    "## Troubleshooting\\n",
    "\\n",
    "### Issue: \\"docling is not installed\\"\\n",
    "**Solution**: Install docling in your virtual environment:\\n",
    "```bash\\n",
    "cd mcp_project\\n",
    "uv add docling  # or: pip install docling\\n",
    "```\\n",
    "\\n",
    "### Issue: \\"File not found\\" errors\\n",
    "**Solution**: Ensure you're using the correct relative path from the `mcp_project` folder:\\n",
    "- Use `../excel_files/filename.xlsx` instead of `excel_files/filename.xlsx`\\n",
    "- Or set the absolute path: `file_path`: `/full/path/to/excel_files/filename.xlsx`\\n",
    "\\n",
    "### Issue: Python version error\\n",
    "**Solution**: MCP requires Python 3.10+. Check your version:\\n",
    "```bash\\n",
    "python3 --version\\n",
    "```\\n",
    "If needed, install Python 3.11:\\n",
    "```bash\\n",
    "# macOS\\n",
    "brew install python@3.11\\n",
    "\\n",
    "# From mcp_project folder, recreate venv with Python 3.11\\n",
    "rm -rf .venv\\n",
    "uv venv --python python3.11\\n",
    "```\\n",
    "\\n",
    "### Issue: Inspector won't connect\\n",
    "**Solution**:\\n",
    "1. Make sure you're running the Inspector from the `mcp_project` folder\\n",
    "2. Check that Node.js is installed: `node --version`\\n",
    "3. Try specifying the full path to the server file\\n",
    "4. Verify the command and arguments in Inspector settings"
   ]
